l two birds with one stone,\u201d offering a practical and flexible solution to the design problem while improving the image of the park with a Romantic touch. The building is envisioned as gates to the park on its north side. Up to now, the park simply ends in front of city buildings. Designed in regulated harmonies of the Golden Section and cubical spaces, the building will, from the bottom of the park, give noble focus to the view uphill. When entering from the north, the building will mark the beginning of the park and offer itself as majestic entrance. With its quiet brick expression, deep shadows in the gates and unruly roof vegetation amongst the park trees, the building may seem to some a natural presence in the park, perhaps reminiscent of a landscape by Claude Lorrain or Francesco Guardi. By creating both a day care building and gates to the park, the project is transformed into a hybrid of a building in the city and urban infrastructure, legitimizing this way its presence in the park.","post_title":"<p>Daycare, St. Gallen, CH 2015<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"daycare-st-gallen-ch-2015","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2017-05-16 19:31:33","post_modified_gmt":"2017-05-16 19:31:33","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=1216","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw"},{"ID":1061,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2017-04-04 20:45:44","post_date_gmt":"2017-04-04 20:45:44","post_content":"Obra acknowledges the shared authorship of architecture, not only a collective activity within any studio, but also an activity dependent on the generosity of a given community\u2019s collective unconscious. We believe subtle interpersonal chemistries decide the success or failure of projects. Conventionally a sketchbook might seem personal, but the displaced logic of the pages set loose from their bindings in this exhibit remove any presumption of coherent personal logic, and serves as a device to correct the record for good. Drawings are deployed on easels suspended from the ceiling allowing double-sided examination. The easels bookend the space with a shy monumentality. The layout follows an ABABA classical rhythm, where A stands for people visiting the gallery and B for drawings of another architecture hanging from the ceiling.","post_title":"<p>Exquisite Corpse, Berlin, DE 2016<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"exquisite-corpse-berlin-de-2016","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2017-05-16 21:43:06","post_modified_gmt":"2017-05-16 21:43:06","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=1061","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw"},{"ID":942,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2017-04-03 15:11:31","post_date_gmt":"2017-04-03 15:11:31","post_content":"Wim Wenders\u2019 film from 1976, titled in English <em>Kings of the Road<\/em>, features Bruno and Robert in a slow-motion race against death. As you might remember, Robert is rescued by Bruno after an unsuccessful suicide attempt. Running his little Volkswagen into a lake at full speed, Robert sees his attempt at self-destruction frustrated by the car\u2019s refusal to sink. Bruno is an itinerant film projector repairman who wanders around the East-German countryside in his truck in search of small-town kinos with a projector in need of repair or maintenance. Bruno takes Robert under his wing, and from then on the romance of <em>Kings of the Road<\/em> is predicated on friendship, rock \u2018n\u2019 roll, the freedom of \u2018having nothing left to lose\u2019 and a humble but sublime workman-like pursuit of the art in the machine. <em>KINOKRAFT the Floating Cinema project<\/em>, is a vehicle for a slow-motion race against death; against the death of cinema in small towns, against the death of canals in big cities and above all against the death of art as a way of life. It would be good if <em>KINOKRAFT<\/em> could offer even a modest satisfaction to the need for an antidote against the rush and demands for \u2018efficiency\u2019 of today\u2019s life and preserve for us the possibility of time spent drifting about the canals with abandon in pursuit of the dream-like space of film.","post_title":"<p>Floating Cinema, London, UK 2012<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"floating-cinema-london-uk-2012","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2017-05-16 22:44:14","post_modified_gmt":"2017-05-16 22:44:14","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=942","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw"},{"ID":107,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2016-12-29 12:23:17","post_date_gmt":"2016-12-29 12:23:17","post_content":"Obra\u2019s <em>Freedom Park<\/em> complex includes museum, memorial, <em>Garden of Remembrance<\/em> with outdoor gathering space, and administration on a 52-hectare site. As visitors ascend a spiral path, the <em>Witness Memorial<\/em> and <em>Freedom Museum<\/em> are gradually revealed in constantly shifting perspectives. Inspired by the African tradition of carving the graves of important community members from a Baobab trunk, the womb-like memorial and museum echo hollowed-out tree trunks. The memorial, a single \u201ctrunk\u201d set in a clearing of indigenous Sugarbush trees, honors apartheid victims. The Museum is configured as four soaring \u201ctrunks\u201d containing ten gallery spaces that can be traversed in sequence as if fused into one, just as trees in close proximity grow into one.","post_titl