icated agent in the maintenance of a system of order devoted to the daily tasks of separating objects, storing and using them. It was during a survey of existing field conditions that the client was inadvertently unmasked as a meticulous moth hunter after specimens were found scotch-taped to a sheet of paper in recorded order of their capture. A flexible separation between night and day spaces as the client\u2019s basic programmatic requirement, in addition to her secret war on Lepidopters\u2014an order of insects largely divided between subfamilies with either diurnal or nocturnal habits\u2014inspired a direction for the project.","post_title":"<p>Loft on 4th Avenue, New York, US 2000<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"loft-in-chelsea-new-york-us-2000","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2017-05-31 15:50:20","post_modified_gmt":"2017-05-31 15:50:20","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=386","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw"},{"ID":1499,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2017-04-16 21:32:06","post_date_gmt":"2017-04-16 21:32:06","post_content":"The miniaturization of technology affords opportunities to develop micro-enterprises to give people in Venice an alternative to working in a hotel or leaving the city. A string of cooperative buildings for new high-tech light industrial manufacturing can be developed on the underused south shore of La Giudecca, complementing the traditionally working-class neighborhoods of the island. The vertical elements of these buildings would be made of apartment units featuring two and three-bedroom apartments organized to give the building a generic character. The units form a C-shape open to the lagoon while supporting above an inhabitable \u201croof\u201d over the water. This \u201croof\u201d will be structured